A man killed his father by cutting him several times with an axe in Keiyo South, Elgeyo Marakwet county, on Tuesday evening.Edwin Koech, 25, turned himself in at Kipkwen police post following the attack on his 85-year old father.Witnesses said the man was seen leaving their house in Kamelil sublocation with blood stains on his clothes.Area assistant chief Peter Masit said Koech cut his father on the leg and head after a quarrel.He said the details of the attack had not been established but added that Koech had been engaging in criminal activities.The body was taken to Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital mortuary in Eldoret for a postmortem.